{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs32 ReaPack Download Instructions\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This repository is now linked natively in the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.reapack.com"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
ReaPack
}}}
 REAPER extension, the free scripts/packages download manager made by {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://github.com/cfillion/"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
cfillion
}}}
.\line This means that you don't need to download and install the scripts manually anymore, you can simply use ReaPack to batch download all scripts or scripts of your choice right from REAPER!\line More, you will get auto-update each time your synchronize packages!\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs32 Manual ReaPack Installation\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 If for some reasons you deleted the link to this repo from ReaPack, you can add it back by importing the following {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/X-Raym/REAPER-ReaScripts/master/index.xml"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
index.xml
}}}
 link from the Import a repository window.\line {\f1 https://raw.githubusercontent.com/X-Raym/REAPER-ReaScripts/master/index.xml}\par}
